You are extending a Fourier Neural Operator (FNO) pipeline to solve the
Tissue Strain Mapping (TSM) problem from MR Elastography. This is a
classical acoustoelasticity problem: an expanding mass creates a
pre-stress field in surrounding tissue that modifies local shear wave
speed. The FNO must recover both the isotropic stiffness field G(x,y)
AND the perilesional latent strain field ε_latent(x,y) from measured
displacement data u(x,y).

The physics: G_measured(x,y) = G₀(x,y) + A · ε_latent(x,y)
where A is the acoustoelastic constant (~-3G₀ to -10G₀ for soft tissue).
The stiffening ring around an expanding lesion is the signature of
ε_latent ≠ 0 in the perilesional zone.

Do not assume any existing code. Build everything from scratch.
Verify each module before proceeding to the next.

