## MODULE 1: Phantom geometry (src/phantom/geometry.py)

### 1a. Lesion geometry
Generate a random lesion (expanding inclusion) embedded in background tissue.

class LesionGeometry:
    Parameters (all randomized per sample):
      center:     (cx, cy) — random in [N/3, 2N/3]
      semi_axes:  (a, b) — major a ~ Uniform(6, N/5), minor b ~ Uniform(0.6a, a)
      angle:      rotation ~ Uniform(0, π)
      pressure:   p ~ Uniform(500, 8000) Pa  (expansion pressure)
                  p=0 reserved for non-expanding control cases (20% probability)

    Methods:
      .mask(N):       returns bool (N,N) array — True inside lesion
      .boundary_normals(N): returns (N,N,2) array of outward unit normals
                            at each point, computed from distance transform
                            (zero inside lesion)
      .distance_field(N):   returns (N,N) array of distance from lesion
                            surface in metres (zero inside lesion)

### 1b. Lamé pre-stress field
Analytical pre-stress field around an elliptical pressurized inclusion.
Use the Eshelby solution for ellipsoidal inclusions in an isotropic matrix.

For a circular inclusion of equivalent radius a_eq = sqrt(a*b) at pressure p:

    σ_rr(r)  = -p · (a_eq/r)²     [radial, compressive]
    σ_θθ(r)  = +p · (a_eq/r)²     [circumferential, tensile]

    Δσ_acoustic(r) = σ_θθ - σ_rr = 2p · (a_eq/r)²

For points inside the lesion: Δσ_acoustic = p (uniform pressure, Lamé)
For points outside: decay as (a_eq/r)²

Function: compute_lame_field(geometry: LesionGeometry, N: int, dx: float)
Returns: (N,N) float64 array of Δσ_acoustic in Pa
         Normalised by G_background so units are dimensionless strain.

### 1c. Shell mask
Generate perilesional annular shell mask for evaluation:

Function: perilesional_shell(lesion_mask, shell_mm, dx)
  shell_mm: shell thickness in mm (default 5mm = 2.5 voxels at 2mm)
  Returns: bool (N,N) — True in annular ring immediately outside lesion

