## MODULE 2: Acoustoelastic phantom (src/phantom/acoustoelastic.py)

This is the core physics module. It generates the spatially varying
effective stiffness field G_eff(x,y) that the wave solver sees.

### 2a. Background stiffness map
G_bg: float — uniform background, ~ Uniform(800, 3000) Pa
G_lesion: float — lesion core stiffness ~ Uniform(3000, 15000) Pa
          (lesion core is stiffer than background — tumor mechanical property)

### 2b. Acoustoelastic stiffness perturbation
The pre-stress field perturbs the local shear modulus via:

    G_eff(x,y) = G_bg(x,y) + A_coeff · Δσ_acoustic(x,y)

where:
    A_coeff ~ Uniform(-8.0, -2.0)   [acoustoelastic constant, dimensionless]
                                     negative because compression softens,
                                     tension stiffens (for tissue convention)
    Δσ_acoustic from Lamé field above

IMPORTANT: The stiffening ring lives in the perilesional zone where
Δσ_acoustic > 0 (circumferential tension). G_eff > G_bg there.
Inside the lesion: different mechanics, handled separately.

### 2c. Full effective stiffness map
def make_effective_G(N, dx, geometry, G_bg, G_lesion, A_coeff):
    G = np.full((N,N), G_bg)                    # background
    G[geometry.mask(N)] = G_lesion              # lesion core
    lame = compute_lame_field(geometry, N, dx)  # pre-stress field
    G += A_coeff * lame * G_bg                  # acoustoelastic perturbation
    G = np.clip(G, 200, 80000)                  # physical bounds [Pa]
    return G

### 2d. Ground truth strain field (training label)
The latent strain label is:

    ε_latent(x,y) = Δσ_acoustic(x,y) / G_bg   [dimensionless]

This is what the second FNO output head must predict.
It is nonzero ONLY in the perilesional shell for expanding lesions (p>0).
It is identically zero everywhere for control cases (p=0).

