## MODULE 4: Wave solver (src/solver/helmholtz_fd.py)

2D time-harmonic Helmholtz equation with spatially varying G:
    ∇·(G*(x,y) ∇u) + ρω²u = 0

IDENTICAL to Phase 0 solver. Reproduce exactly:

Parameters:
    rho    = 1000.0   kg/m³
    dx     = 0.002    m
    freq1  = 60.0     Hz  (primary)
    freq2  = 120.0    Hz  (second harmonic — improves ε_latent recovery)
    damping = 0.05    (loss tangent)

Boundary conditions:
    Left column j=0: u = exp(i·φ_source) where φ_source ~ Uniform(0, 2π)
                     (random source phase — augmentation, prevents
                      model learning boundary artifacts)
    All other edges: u = 0

Add noise at SNR ~ Uniform(15, 30) dB to output displacement.

Solve at BOTH frequencies. Return 4-channel complex displacement:
    [Re(u_60Hz), Im(u_60Hz), Re(u_120Hz), Im(u_120Hz)]

