## MODULE 5: Training data generation (src/data/generate_tsm.py)

### 5a. Full training pair
def make_tsm_pair(N=64, dx=0.002, rng=None):
    Generates ONE complete training sample.

    Returns:
      X: float32 (6, N, N) — 6 input channels:
         Ch 0-3: displacement [Re(u₆₀), Im(u₆₀), Re(u₁₂₀), Im(u₁₂₀)]
         Ch 4:   Lamé pre-stress field Δσ (analytical prior)
         Ch 5:   Distance from lesion surface (normalised 0-1)

         IMPORTANT: Channels 4 and 5 are the physics-informed inputs.
         They tell the FNO WHERE the lesion is and what the analytical
         pre-stress field looks like. This dramatically reduces the
         learning problem and enforces the Lamé geometry.

      Y: dict with two labels:
         'G':       float32 (N,N) — effective stiffness G_eff [Pa]
         'epsilon':  float32 (N,N) — latent strain ε_latent [dimensionless]
                     zero everywhere for control (p=0) cases

      meta: dict with:
         'p': expansion pressure [Pa] (0 for control)
         'A': acoustoelastic constant
         'G_bg': background stiffness
         'G_lesion': lesion core stiffness
         'a_eq': equivalent lesion radius [m]
         'is_expanding': bool

### 5b. Dataset composition
Target: 50,000 total samples with the following distribution:
    60%  — actively expanding lesions (p > 0, clear stiffening ring)
    20%  — non-expanding lesions (p = 0, no ring — control)
    10%  — high-contrast inclusions (G_lesion/G_bg > 10, hard cases)
    10%  — near-isotropic (a ≈ b, circular — easier geometry)

This composition ensures the model learns to DISTINGUISH expanding
from non-expanding lesions — the core clinical question.

### 5c. HDF5 format
Each chunk file: data/chunks/tsm_chunk_{task_id:04d}.h5
    /X          float32 (chunk_size, 6, N, N)
    /Y_G        float32 (chunk_size, N, N)
    /Y_epsilon  float32 (chunk_size, N, N)
    /meta/p              float32 (chunk_size,)
    /meta/A              float32 (chunk_size,)
    /meta/G_bg           float32 (chunk_size,)
    /meta/is_expanding   bool    (chunk_size,)

