## MODULE 7: Loss functions (src/model/losses.py)

### 7a. Stiffness loss (identical to Phase 0)
L_G = relative L² loss on G prediction:
    L_G = mean(||G_pred - G_true||₂ / ||G_true||₂)   over batch

### 7b. Latent strain loss
L_eps = weighted relative L² on ε_latent:
    L_eps = mean(||ε_pred - ε_true||₂ / (||ε_true||₂ + ε_floor))

where ε_floor = 0.001 prevents division by zero for control cases (p=0).

IMPORTANT: Weight the perilesional shell MORE than background:
    shell_mask = perilesional_shell(lesion_mask, shell_mm=5.0, dx=0.002)
    L_eps_ring = relative_l2(ε_pred[shell_mask], ε_true[shell_mask])
    L_eps_bg   = relative_l2(ε_pred[~shell_mask], ε_true[~shell_mask])
    L_eps      = 0.7 * L_eps_ring + 0.3 * L_eps_bg

This forces the model to get the stiffening ring right even if the
background ε≈0 everywhere would give a low overall loss.

### 7c. Acoustoelastic consistency loss
Enforces the physical coupling G_eff = G₀ + A · ε_latent:

    G_bg_pred = G_pred * (1 - lesion_mask)   (background only)
    G_ring    = G_bg_pred * shell_mask

    G_reconstructed = G_bg_mean + A_pred · eps_pred
    L_acoustic = MSE(G_reconstructed[shell_mask], G_pred[shell_mask])

where A_pred is an additional scalar output (learned per-sample
acoustoelastic constant). Add a third micro-head for A_pred:
    self.A_fc = nn.Linear(width, 1)   (single scalar, global pooling)
    A_pred = -softplus(global_avg_pool(trunk_features) → A_fc) - 2.0
    (negative, bounded below -2.0 per tissue physics)

### 7d. Helmholtz PDE residual loss (from Phase 0)
    L_pde = Helmholtz residual on G_pred and u_input
    (reuse HelmholtzResidual class from Phase 0)

### 7e. Expansion detection loss
Binary classification: is this an expanding lesion?

    expansion_score = max(eps_pred[shell_mask])
    expanding_true  = (p > 0).float()
    L_expand = BCE(sigmoid(expansion_score / ε_threshold), expanding_true)

where ε_threshold = 0.01 (detection floor).

This forces the model to produce ε≈0 for control cases even if the
wave field looks similar to an expanding case.

### 7f. Total loss
    L_total = L_G
            + λ_eps    · L_eps         (λ_eps    = 1.0)
            + λ_ring   · L_eps_ring    (λ_ring   = 0.5, extra weight on ring)
            + λ_acoustic · L_acoustic  (λ_acoustic = 0.1)
            + λ_pde    · L_pde         (λ_pde    = 0.05)
            + λ_expand · L_expand      (λ_expand  = 0.2)

Return all components as a dict for logging.

